{
  "texts": [
    "A common theme to all categories of algorithm is ensembling.",
    "Another popular method seen in multiple classifiers are transformation pipelines ending with a linear classifier.",
    "The most accurate classifiers we find all form homogeneous or heterogeneous ensembles, or extract features prior to a linear ridge classifier.",
    "To try and capture the commonality and differences between algorithms we provide a Table in the Appendix B (Table 22) that groups algorithms by whether they employ the following design characteristics: dilation; discretisation; differences/derivatives; frequency domain; ensemble; and linear classification.",
    "We review each category of algorithms by providing an overview of the approach, review selected classifiers and describe the pattern they use, starting with the best of class from the bake off."
  ]
}